#Method bool readPixels(const SkIRect& srcRect, SkBitmap* bitmap)

Copies pixels enclosed by srcRect from Canvas into bitmap, converting their Color_Type and Alpha_Type.
Pixels are readable when Device is raster. Pixels are not readable when Canvas is returned from
GPU_Surface or obtained from Document-based Canvas or other Canvas subclasses.
Allocates pixel storage in bitmap if needed.

Pixel values are converted only if Canvas Color_Type and Alpha_Type does not match bitmap Image_Info.
Only pixels within the rectangle that intersect Canvas pixels are copied.
dstPixels outside the rectangle intersection are unchanged.

 #Table
#Legend
# canvas pixel bounds # value ##
##
# left # 0 ##
# top # 0 ##
# width # SkCanvas::info.width() ##
# height # SkCanvas::info.height() ##
##

Does not copy, and returns false if:

#List
  srcRect and canvas pixel bounds do not intersect.
  Canvas pixels could not be converted to bitmap Color_Type or bitmap Alpha_Type.
  Canvas pixels are not readable; for instance, Canvas is not raster, or is document-based.
  bitmap pixels could not be allocated.
  bitmap Row_Bytes is too small to contain one row of pixels. 
##

#Param srcRect  Subset of Canvas readable pixels. ##
